ation (to repeat) in a human particular creates what we call Christ \"two but one natures - wholly God + wholly man person.\" Thus we use the term \"Christ\" for this precise situation of instantiating, Jesus being the first one. However, only the human nature is pluralized (differing from particular to particular) the God-nature is unitary, is one for them all This the organic \"body\" model that Paul proposes, in which we are parts but Christ is - + supra-spation This supernatural the head temporal - body is distributed across space + time but possessing one ruling psyche; to there is but one Christ. Thus (as I repeat, conceive it) a superorganism is created, not space, time, causality, by any one bound b I K-19 locus, gathering in more + more \"particulars\" as history unfolds. This vast psychosomatic organism grows ever more complex. It is its own Kingdom; hence the more precise word is \"Kingship,\" expressing its rule, rather than a geographic spatial area/region, with frontiers. This it does not merely invade + transubstantiate the physical universe but humans primarily, incorporating them in the camouflaged way that I saw Valis doing (which is why I also experienced Valis in me as a super-mind as well as something very vast outside). This line of reasoning is not nonsense; for one thing it renders clear many crucial but is puzzling statements in the N.T. Now, here another point unless or until I figured this \"inner\" part out, \"Christ in us,\" as Paul puts would not really have understood 2-3-74 it, I that is, my belief that in seeing Valis exter‐ nally I saw the cosmic Christ is only half the story + perhaps the lesser half. However, it is just as well that in writing \"Valis\" I did not claim to \"be\" Christ, only to have seen him psychotic inflation of the ego is frowned on, even by the amiable). This all of course collates perfectly with \"receiving the Holy Spirit\" at the reperformance by the apostles of the Lord's supper. (\"Baptism in The Spirit,\