    {
      "text": "Last edit almost 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n83\nNeeds Review\n83\nG-84 Torah, which programs the world? This is info of a topic I feel a lot of anxiety about. control is a frightening idea, as is the idea that our normal existence may be that of occluded, programmed machines - programmed by instructions we can't see, whose existence we do not suspect. It has the power to compel our assent (to reality). Then the meta-abstraction is: a realization is that my assent is compelled to what in fai only i",
